cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on cluster-based routing in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a modified version of the LEACH protocol for wireless sensor networks, which involves distributed and cluster-based computing. 

3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The use of cluster-based routing in wireless sensor networks involves the coordination and communication of multiple agents, which falls under the domain of multiagent systems. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a modified routing protocol for wireless sensor networks, which involves the control and management of the network system. 

5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the primary focus of the paper, the use of wireless sensor networks raises security concerns, which may fall under the domain of cryptography and security.
